==Latin==
===Suffix===
'''-udo''', '''[[-udinis]]''', ''f''

Third declension

# suffix appended to words, particularly adjectives, to form nouns naming a state of being.  Similar to suffix ''[[-itas]]''.

====Examples====


{| border="2" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0"
|-----
| Adjective || Noun of state
|-----
| gratis || gratitudo
|-----
| solus || solitudo
|}

